Introduction

Jvcki Wai, born Hong Ye-eun, is a South Korean rapper who debuted on November 2, 2016, with mini-album “Exposure” under The Ugly Junction and STONESHIP. As an artist, she's known for her war-like lyrics with colorful layers of synths with energetically delivered verses and post-cyberpunk styling and themes.

In 2018 she signed to Swings' label 'INDIGO Music', and went on to release her first studio full-length album 'Enchanted Propaganda'.
In October 2019, she left INDIGO as her contract had expired, only releasing two collaboration singles after her departure.

On October 24, 2022, it was announced that Jvcki Wai had signed with Jay Park's label 'AOMG' and released her first song in two years, 'Go Back'.
